OL,3,CWhat we know about the deadly pager
OL,4,Cexplosions in Lebanon
OL,6,FThis strategy would give operatives a
OL,7,Fchance to insert explosives and modify
OL,8,Fthe software of the pagers,
OL,9,Fpotentially to react to a particular
OL,10,Fmessage or signal to trigger an
OL,11,Fexplosion, Mr Billois says.
OL,13,F"The most likely scenario is an
OL,14,Finterception of the shipment at some
OL,15,Fpoint in the supply chain, where the
OL,16,Fboxes were carefully opened, modified,
OL,17,Fand then resealed with new packaging.
