OL,3,CWhat we know about the deadly pager
OL,4,Cexplosions in Lebanon
OL,6,F"While overheating batteries could
OL,7,Fpotentially cause a fire, the images
OL,8,Fcirculating of the explosions indicate
OL,9,Fsomething more severe," says Mr
OL,10,FBillois.
OL,12,F"Batteries generally burn rather than
OL,13,Fexplode in the manner witnessed. It's
OL,14,Fpossible that an explosive charge was
OL,15,Fadded to the pagers, and the software
OL,16,Fwas altered to react to a specific
OL,17,Fmessage, which could have triggered
OL,18,Fthe explosions."
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G9/22
