OL,3,CWhat we know about the deadly pager
OL,4,Cexplosions in Lebanon
OL,6,FDr Krieg suggests the explosives were
OL,7,F"activated remotely by a particular
OL,8,Fmessage that could have caused the
OL,9,Fbattery to heat and then activate the
OL,10,Fexplosives inside the device".
OL,12,FHowever, Mr Billois isn't convinced by
OL,13,Fthis theory, saying it "seems more
OL,14,Flikely that a specific message was
OL,15,Fused" to detonate the explosives
OL,16,Fdirectly.
