OL,6,FN.R. Jenzen-Jones, an expert in
OL,7,Fmilitary arms and director of the
OL,8,FAustralian-based Armament Research
OL,9,FServices agrees that such a large-
OL,10,Fscale operation "raises questions of
OL,11,Ftargeting" ` stressing the number of
OL,12,Fcausalities and enormous impact
OL,13,Freported so far.
OL,15,F"How can the party initiating the
OL,16,Fexplosive be sure that a target's
OL,17,Fchild, for example, is not playing
OL,18,Fwith the pager at the time it
OL,19,Ffunctions?" he says.
