OL,3,CWhat we know about the deadly pager
OL,4,Cexplosions in Lebanon
OL,6,FAn attack of this calibre requires
OL,7,Fbuilding the relationships needed to
OL,8,Fgain physical access to the pagers
OL,9,Fbefore they were sold, developing the
OL,10,Ftechnology that would be embedded in
OL,11,Fthe devices, and developing sources
OL,12,Fwho can confirm that the targets were
OL,13,Fcarrying the pagers.
OL,15,FIt is also likely the compromised
OL,16,Fpagers seemed normal to their users
OL,17,Ffor some time before the attack.
