OL,3,CWhat we know about the deadly pager
OL,4,Cexplosions in Lebanon
OL,6,FBased on his conversations with
OL,7,FHezbollah members, Mr Magnier also
OL,8,Fsaid that many pagers didn't go off,
OL,9,Fallowing the group to inspect them.
OL,10,FThey came to the conclusion that three
OL,11,Fto five grams of a highly explosive
OL,12,Fmaterial were concealed or embedded in
OL,13,Fthe circuitry, he said.
OL,15,FHezbollah already changed their
OL,16,Fcommunication strategies by replacing
OL,17,Fmobile phones with pagers, and Reese
OL,18,Fsuggests the group will now have to
OL,19,Fthink again following the latest
OL,20,Fattacks.
